<div id="review_160314466" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/160314466" />
    <a title="Tyler Koslow" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4837860-tyler-koslow"><img alt="Tyler Koslow" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1297118728p2/4837860.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/160314466?book_show_action=true">Apr 11, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tyler Koslow" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tyler Koslow" href="/user/show/4837860-tyler-koslow">Tyler Koslow</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer160314466" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15701547136769964932">Bukowski&apos;s collection of short stories address the destructive and lonely nature of human existence. This is usually made by most writers in an extravagant, fiction-like manner, but Charles Bukowski brings destruction into his work through the normal, everyday dirty work that portrays the dark side to human achievement and society. His collection helped me realize that my ideal, no matter how surreal, can still be found in everyday observations on human life. This type of realism that he uses he</span>
  <span id="freeText15701547136769964932" style="display:none">Bukowski's collection of short stories address the destructive and lonely nature of human existence. This is usually made by most writers in an extravagant, fiction-like manner, but Charles Bukowski brings destruction into his work through the normal, everyday dirty work that portrays the dark side to human achievement and society. His collection helped me realize that my ideal, no matter how surreal, can still be found in everyday observations on human life. This type of realism that he uses helps the reader connect his vague depression to the tiny ordeals of everyday life.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15701547136769964932" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


