        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2429034680" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7150722767270504904">Just like every Charles Bukowski short story collection, they are hit or miss. The hits make up for the misses, the times when his writing is on point; you&apos;ll find everything you love about him in those stories. The misses are so bad, that even though they&apos;re generally quite short, I found myself skipping over the especially bad ones. Bukowski really shines in writing novels where everything is more focused, I&apos;d highly recommend those if you&apos;re new to him.</span>
  <span id="freeText7150722767270504904" style="display:none">Just like every Charles Bukowski short story collection, they are hit or miss. The hits make up for the misses, the times when his writing is on point; you'll find everything you love about him in those stories. The misses are so bad, that even though they're generally quite short, I found myself skipping over the especially bad ones. Bukowski really shines in writing novels where everything is more focused, I'd highly recommend those if you're new to him.</span>
