  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/829427899" />
    <a title="John M." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6984092-john-m"><img alt="John M." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1380888923p2/6984092.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/829427899?book_show_action=true">Jan 20, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John M." class="user" itemprop="url" name="John M." href="/user/show/6984092-john-m">John M.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6984092-john-m?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6984092-john-m?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6984092-john-m?shelf=2014-reading-challenge">2014-reading-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6984092-john-m?shelf=dirty-realism">dirty-realism</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer829427899" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5851584116082714755"><br/>I&apos;ve read a number of Bukowski&apos;s other books, and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50453.Hot_Water_Music' title='Hot Water Music by Charles Bukowski' rel='nofollow noopener'>Hot Water Music</a> just didn&apos;t appeal to me like the others. It&apos;s a collection of short stories that essentially repeat the same formula over and over again. In fact, a lot of these stories could be inserted as chapters in <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1934.Little_Women__Little_Women___1_' title='Little Women (Little Women, #1) by Louisa May Alcott' rel='nofollow noopener'>Women</a>, which in my opinion is the weakest of the Bukowski novels. <br/><br/>Even though it&apos;s just over 200 pages long, it was a tedious read, aside from a small handful of stories. If you&apos;re new to Bukowski, read <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/38501.Ham_on_Rye' title='Ham on Rye by Charles Bukowski' rel='nofollow noopener'>Ham on Rye</a> or <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51504.Post_Office' title='Post Office by Charles Bukowski' rel='nofollow noopener'>Post Office</a>, </span>
  <span id="freeText5851584116082714755" style="display:none"><br />I've read a number of Bukowski's other books, and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50453.Hot_Water_Music" title="Hot Water Music by Charles Bukowski" rel="nofollow noopener">Hot Water Music</a> just didn't appeal to me like the others. It's a collection of short stories that essentially repeat the same formula over and over again. In fact, a lot of these stories could be inserted as chapters in <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1934.Little_Women__Little_Women___1_" title="Little Women (Little Women, #1) by Louisa May Alcott" rel="nofollow noopener">Women</a>, which in my opinion is the weakest of the Bukowski novels. <br /><br />Even though it's just over 200 pages long, it was a tedious read, aside from a small handful of stories. If you're new to Bukowski, read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/38501.Ham_on_Rye" title="Ham on Rye by Charles Bukowski" rel="nofollow noopener">Ham on Rye</a> or <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51504.Post_Office" title="Post Office by Charles Bukowski" rel="nofollow noopener">Post Office</a>, and skip this collection. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5851584116082714755" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
